ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Now I need to create `matching-common.js` with real step implementati
ons, and update the 4 `.steps.js` files. Let me also create a `matching-helpers.
js` similar to `auth-helpers.js`.\n\nGiven the complexity, let me write a compre
hensive `matching-common.js` that covers all the matching scenarios across all 4
feature files. Then each `.steps.js` will use `autoBindSteps(feature, [matchingC
ommonSteps])`.\n\nActually, looking at how `autoBindSteps` works, it should matc
h step definitions by regex. But `common.js` already defines empty implementatio
ns for matching steps. If I create `matching-common.js` and have the `.steps.js`
use it instead of `common.js`, the empty steps won\'t interfere.\n\nWait, `autoB
indSteps` binds steps from multiple step definition files. If both `common.js` a
nd `matching-common.js` define the same step, there might be a conflict. It\'s s
afer to use `defineFeature` in each `.steps.js` file.\n\nLet me create `matching
-common.js` that exports step definitions, and then each `.steps.js` will use `d
efineFeature` and call the appropriate step definitions.\n\nActually, looking at
`auth_login_phone_number_login.steps.js`, it uses `defineFeature` directly and i
mplements steps inline. For matching, I can do a hybrid: create `matching-common
.js` with helper functions and context, then each `.steps.js` uses `defineFeatur
e` with inline step definitions that call helpers.\n\nBut that\'s still a lot of
code. Let me look at what `autoBindSteps` actually does. According to jest-cucum
ber docs, `autoBindSteps` takes an array of step definition functions and automa
tically binds them to scenarios. Each step definition function receives `{ given
, when, then, and }` and registers its steps.\n\nIf I pass only `[matchingCommon
Steps]` to `autoBindSteps`, it won\'t include `commonSteps`. So there shouldn\'t
be conflicts.\n\nLet me write `matching-common.js` with all the matching step de
finitions.\n\nBut wait - `autoBindSteps` requires that ALL steps in the feature 
file have corresponding step definitions. If `matching-common.js` doesn\'t defin
e all steps used in the feature files, it will error.\n\nLooking at the 4 featur
e files, the steps are:\n1. `matching_card_recommendations.feature`:\n   - Given
the user is on the home screen with a complete profile\n   - And there are 20 el
igible candidates nearby\n   - When the app requests GET /matching/recommendatio
ns\n   - Then the user should receive a stack of up to 20 profile cards\n   - An
d each card should contain: user_id, nickname, age, distance, bio, avatar_url\n 
 - And the cards should be sorted by composite score\n   - Given the user has re
quested recommendations within the last 5 minutes\n   - When the app requests GE
T /matching/recommendations again\n   - Then the API should return cached result
s from Redis within 100ms\n   - Given the user is in a remote area with no other
users\n   - When the app requests recommendations\n   - Then the API should retu
rn an empty list\n   - And the app should show an empty state "附近暂无可推荐用
户"\n\n2. `matching_swipe_actions.feature`:\n   - Given the user sees a card for
target user "Bob"\n   - When the user swipes right or taps the like button\n   -
Then a like action should be recorded in match_actions\n   - And the target user
should be removed from the user\'s recommendation cache\n   - Given the user see
s a card for target user "Charlie"\n   - When the user swipes left or taps the p
ass button\n   - Then a pass action should be recorded in match_actions\n   - An
d the target user should be removed from the user\'s recommendation cache\n   - 
Given the user has already liked target user "Bob"\n   - When the user likes "Bo
b" again within 1 second\n   - Then the API should return success without creati
ng a duplicate match_actions record\n   - And no duplicate match should be creat
ed\n   - Given the user sees their own profile in the candidate list by accident
\n   - When the user tries to like themselves\n   - Then the API should reject w
ith code 1000\n\n3. `matching_mutual_like_creates_match.feature`:\n   - Given Al
ice liked Bob\n   - And Bob has not yet liked Alice\n   - When Bob likes Alice\n
  - Then a match record should be created with status "matched"\n   - And a conv
ersation should be auto-created for Alice and Bob\n   - And both users should re
ceive a match notification via Socket.io\n   - And both users should see the new
match in their match list\n   - Given Alice liked Bob\n   - And Bob has not like
d Alice\n   - When the system checks for mutual like\n   - Then no match record 
should exist\n   - And no conversation should be created\n\n4. `matching_match_l
ist.feature`:\n   - Given Alice has matched with Bob and Charlie\n   - When Alic
e opens the match list\n   - Then she should see Bob and Charlie ordered by matc
