lows/matching/recommendations.yaml`\n2. `.maestro/flows/matching/swipe_and_match
.yaml`\n\nI also need to make sure the components in the mobile app have proper 
Semantics identifiers for Maestro to find them.\n\nLooking at the HomePage, the 
mode selector now uses `SwModeSelector` which has `identifier: \'mode_selector\'
`. The swipe card stack and action buttons have identifiers from the design syst
em.\n\nBut I need to verify that `SwipeCard` and the card stack area have proper
identifiers for Maestro. Let me check what identifiers exist in the current flow
.\n\nLooking at HomePage:\n- `_CardStackArea` doesn\'t have a Semantics identifi
er\n- The `SwipeCard` doesn\'t have a Semantics identifier\n- The `EmptyRecommen
dationView` might need one\n\nFor Maestro tests, I should add Semantics to key c
omponents. But the review specifically mentions:\n- "进入首页 → 断言卡片可见 → 
切换 mode → 断言空状态或卡片更新"\n- "右滑卡片 → 断言匹配成功弹窗 → 点击「开始聊
天」→ 断言进入匹配列表"\n\nFor the card visibility, I can assert on text content
(like the nickname on the card). For mode switching, I can tap on `mode_selector
