p definition(s) defined." This means `autoBindSteps` can\'t match some steps.\n\
nLooking at the errors:\n1. `matching_card_recommendations.feature`: step "there
are 20 eligible candidates nearby" - in my code I defined `given(\'there are 20 
eligible candidates nearby\', ...)` but the feature file says `And there are 20 
eligible candidates nearby`. `autoBindSteps` might expect `given` to match `And`
steps that follow a `Given`.\n\nWait, in `jest-cucumber`, `autoBindSteps` should
match `And` steps using the same keyword function (`given`, `when`, `then`). But
maybe the issue is that I have duplicate step definitions or missing ones.\n\nAc
tually, looking at the error output more carefully:\n- "User sees their matches"
has 4 step(s), but 2 step definition(s) defined.\n\nLet me check what step defin
itions are found vs what\'s in the feature file.\n\nFor `matching_match_list.fea
ture`:\n```\n  Given Alice has matched with Bob and Charlie\n  When Alice opens 
the match list\n  Then she should see Bob and Charlie ordered by match creation 
time descending\n  And each item should show the matched user\'s nickname, avata
r, and match time\n```\n\nIn `matching-common.js`, I have:\n- `given(\'Alice has
matched with Bob and Charlie\', ...)` \n- `when(\'Alice opens the match list\', 
...)`\n- `aliasThenAnd(\'she should see Bob and Charlie ordered by match creatio
n time descending\', ...)`\n- `aliasThenAnd(\'each item should show the matched 
user\\\'s nickname, avatar, and match time\', ...)`\n\nBut `aliasThenAnd` calls 
`then(pattern, fn)` and `and(pattern, fn)`. Since `and` is the same function ref
erence as `then` in jest-cucumber (they\'re aliases), calling `and` with the sam
e pattern might be okay.\n\nWait, but in `autoBindSteps`, if I call `then(\'she 
should see...\')` and `and(\'she should see...\')`, that registers the SAME step
twice. That might not be the issue.\n\nThe real issue might be that some of my s
tep patterns don\'t match exactly. For example:\n- Feature: `Given Alice has mat
ched with Bob and Charlie`\n- My code: `given(\'Alice has matched with Bob and C
harlie\', ...)`\n\nThat should match.\n\nWait, looking at `matching-common.js`, 
I see the issue! For `matching_swipe_actions.feature`:\n- Feature: `Given the us
er sees a card for target user "Bob"`\n- My code: `given(\'the user sees a card 
