er parameter type. But `autoBindSteps` might not support parameterized steps pro
perly? Actually, `autoBindSteps` DOES support parameterized steps. The issue mig
ht be elsewhere.\n\nActually, looking at the error for `matching_swipe_actions.s
teps.js`:\n"Scenario \'User likes a profile\' has 4 step(s), but 1 step definiti
on(s) defined."\n\nThis means only 1 step definition was found for that scenario
. Let me look at what steps are in the feature file:\n```\n  Given the user sees
