on\n  Then a like action should be recorded in match_actions\n  And the target u
ser should be removed from the user\'s recommendation cache\n```\n\nIn `matching
-common.js`, I have:\n- `given(\'the user sees a card for target user {string}\'
, ...)` - this is parameterized\n- `when(\'the user swipes right or taps the lik
e button\', ...)`\n- `aliasThenAnd(\'a like action should be recorded in match_a
ctions\', ...)`\n- `aliasThenAnd(\'the target user should be removed from the us
er\\\'s recommendation cache\', ...)`\n\nWait, but `aliasThenAnd` registers with
BOTH `then` and `and`. The last step in the feature is `And`, which should match
the `then` registration because `and` is an alias for `then` in jest-cucumber.\n
\nHmm, let me look at the `matching-common.js` file more carefully. I remember t
here was a duplicate `given(\'the user sees a card for target user {string}\', .
..)` definition - one in the swipe actions section and one in the pass section. 
Could duplicate step definitions cause `autoBindSteps` to fail?\n\nActually, loo
king at the jest-cucumber source for `autoBindSteps`, duplicate step definitions
might cause the second one to overwrite the first, but they should still be regi
stered.\n\nWait, I think I found the issue. In `matching-common.js`, I have dupl
icate `given(\'the user sees a card for target user {string}\', ...)` definition
s. The first one is for the "like" scenario, the second is for the "pass" scenar
io. In jest-cucumber, if you register the same step pattern twice, the second re
gistration overwrites the first. But both should still be available... actually 
