alized as `jest.fn()`. When `getServer()` is called, it returns the same mock ob
ject. But `matching-helpers.js` calls `profileRepo.findOne.mockImplementation(..
.)` which changes the implementation. This should persist.\n\n   But wait, `getM
atches` also calls `conversationRepo.findOne`. Let me check if `conversationRepo
` is properly set up in `bdd-setup.js`.\n\n   Looking at `bdd-setup.js`:\n   ```
javascript\n   const mockConversationRepo = {\n     findOne: jest.fn(),\n     in
sert: jest.fn(),\n   };\n   ```\n\n   This is returned by `getServer()`. In `mat
ching-helpers.js`, I access `conversationRepo` from `getServer()`. This should w
ork.\n\n   Let me check the actual response. The error says `item.nickname` is `
""`. Looking at the `getMatches` mock setup in `matching-helpers.js`:\n\n   ```j
avascript\n   matchRepo.createQueryBuilder.mockReturnValue({\n     where: jest.f
n().mockReturnThis(),\n     andWhere: jest.fn().mockReturnThis(),\n     orderBy:
jest.fn().mockReturnThis(),\n     take: jest.fn().mockReturnThis(),\n     getMan
y: jest.fn().mockResolvedValue(matches),\n   });\n   ```\n\n   Wait, `getMatches
` in `matching.service.ts` uses `qb.getMany()` and then iterates over the result
s. The mock returns matches. Then for each match, it calls `profileRepo.findOne`
. \n\n   But wait, `matchRepo` in `bdd-setup.js` is a shared mock object. And `m
atching.service.spec.ts` also mocks `matchRepo.createQueryBuilder`. Could there 
be interference between the unit test mocks and the BDD test mocks?\n\n   Actual
ly, `bdd-setup.js` and `matching.service.spec.ts` create separate TestingModules
. The mock objects in `bdd-setup.js` are separate from those in `matching.servic
e.spec.ts`. But `profileRepo` in `bdd-setup.js` is a single object that\'s reuse
d across all BDD tests.\n\n   The issue might be that `profileRepo.findOne.mockI
mplementation(...)` in `matching-helpers.js` is being overwritten by another tes
